                "description": "The central business district of Beverly Hills, bounded by Santa Monica Boulevard, Wilshire Boulevard, and Canon Drive. The Golden Triangle emerged as the city's commercial core in the 1920s and has remained one of the world's preeminent luxury retail destinations ever since. It encompasses the global flagship boutiques of Rodeo Drive, the celebrated \"Little Restaurant Row\" on North Canon Drive, and the dense concentration of galleries, jewelers, and couturiers that have made Beverly Hills synonymous with high-end commerce.",
