                "lat": 34.1570454,
                "lng": -118.3250084,
                "address": "500 S Buena Vista St, Burbank, CA 91521, USA",
                "description": "Financed by Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937), Disney\u2019s 51-acre Streamline Moderne lot at 500 S Buena Vista opened February 23 1940. Kem Weber\u2019s design placed ink-and-paint labs, a three-story animation building, and Stage 1\u20134 around a central plaza. The studio later expanded with Stages built after the Burbank lot opened in 1940, the Mill Building, and backlot sets for Zorro and Disneyland TV. It served as Walt Disney\u2019s corporate HQ and remains home to Walt Disney Animation, Marvel Studios, and ABC Television.",
