                "description": "Built in 1968, this massive, tri-level indoor marketplace on the East LA / Boyle Heights border was directly modeled after the traditional bustling mercados of Mexico. It was designed to be a comprehensive hub for the community to shop, eat, and gather, complete with roaming mariachi bands and a highly festive atmosphere. Rather than a single restaurant, this is a sprawling culinary destination featuring dozens of independent food stalls, bakeries, and vendors\u2014the perfect place to explore an enormous variety of authentic regional Mexican fare under one roof.",
