                "name": "Maravilla Handball Court (El Centro Community Center)",
                "description": "A true architectural \"marvel,\" this historic brick handball court was built in 1928 and stands as one of the oldest and most significant athletic landmarks in the region. It is a living monument to the community\u2019s spirit, serving for nearly a century as a sacred gathering ground where generations of Eastside residents have perfected the fast-paced game of handball.",
