                "mapUrl": "https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=34.0851337,-118.2527537",
                "description": "The creative heart of one of Los Angeles' most influential living artists, whose work bridges the boundary between fine art and functional design. A founding member of the legendary Milan-based Memphis Group \u2014 the radical 1980s design collective known for its bold colors, geometric postmodernism, and defiant rejection of modernist minimalism \u2014 Shire brought that sensibility home to the Echo Park hills. The studio itself is a visual landmark: bold primary colors and playful structural elements announce it from the street. The distinctive Echo Park teapots and sculptures found in museums and collections worldwide were conceived within these walls.",
