                "description": "The Vibe: This is an early, critical example of Soriano\u2019s \"Steel Modernism.\" Built for Albert and Beulah Ross, it sits on a steep Echo Park lot. It uses a light steel frame and massive bands of windows.\n\nGazetteer Note: This was one of the first homes in L.A. to truly embrace the International Style without the \"softness\" of the regional wood-centric modernism. It's essentially a high-precision glass box floating over a hillside.\n\nAs we noted earlier, this is a foundational Historic-Cultural Monument (#964). It is one of the earliest examples of Soriano\u2019s steel-frame residential work, utilizing light industrial materials to conquer a steep hillside.",
