                "description": "A historic Hollywood landmark whose Gothic-inspired architecture and storied past have made it one of the most atmospheric addresses in the city. A frequent haunt for golden-age stars including Rudolph Valentino and Marilyn Monroe, the Knickerbocker is perhaps most legendarily associated with Harry Houdini's widow, who held rooftop s\u00e9ances annually in an attempt to contact her late husband. Its dark, slightly mysterious Old Hollywood aesthetic has made it a perennial choice for film productions seeking an authentic noir atmosphere, appearing in countless features and television productions over the decades.",
