                "description": "The home and studio of pioneering Austrian-American architect Richard Neutra, and a National Historic Landmark. Built on the edge of the Silver Lake Reservoir, the VDL Research House embodies Neutra's philosophy of \"biorealism\" \u2014 the idea that architecture should blur the boundary between interior and exterior through massive windows, rooftop gardens, and a deep responsiveness to light, water, and landscape. The building is widely credited as the crucible of the \"Silver Lake style\" of light-filled, hillside modernist living that has defined the neighborhood's architectural identity ever since. Now managed by Cal Poly Pomona, it is open for public tours.",
