                "description": "This is the site of the historic Firestone Tire and Rubber Company plant. Designed by the renowned architectural firm Curlett and Beelman (architects of the Eastern Columbia Building) and completed in 1928, it was Firestone\u2019s first manufacturing facility outside of Akron, Ohio. The Italianate-style complex was so central to the city's identity that the main thoroughfare was renamed Firestone Boulevard in honor of Harvey Firestone. While much of the plant has been redeveloped, \"Building 2\" remains a significant historic survivor of the region's \"Rubber Capital\" era.",
